                <h1>Unraveling Virginia Woolf's Influence on "The Yellow Wallpaper"</h1>
                <p>Virginia Woolf and "The Yellow Wallpaper" explore themes of mental health and women's oppression. Although Woolf didn't write this story, the narrative reflects the struggles faced by women in a patriarchal society. The wallpaper symbolizes confinement and the quest for identity, illustrating the impact of society on women's mental states.</p>
